Thousands of music fans have flocked to Worthy Farm for this year’s Glastonbury Festival. The event is the first since the pandemic and is set to be bigger and better than ever with more than 3,000 acts set to perform across the weekend. Today will see the festival’s first huge headline performance from Billie Eilish on the Pyramid Stage ahead of the likes of Kendrick Lamar, Sir Paul McCartney, and Diana Ross. And despite rail strikes set to cause chaos for those heading to the festival and storms threatening to soak revellers, fans are set to enjoy a bumper weekend of arts and entertainment at the iconic event. Planning whose sets to catch at the festival? Here’s who is playing today, along with their performance times and which stage you’ll find them on. Today will see Billie Eilish headline the pyramid stage as the youngest solo headliner of the festival. The acts set to play today include: The full line-up can be found here. MORE : How to watch Glastonbury 2022 at home and full TV schedule MORE : Glastonbury 2022: Here are all the LGBTQ+ acts to watch at this year’s festival Follow Metro across our social channels, on Facebook, Twitter and Instagram Share your views in the comments below 